Through any two distinct points in a [[projective space|Projective space]], there is a unique projective line. The line through $$[v_1],[v_2]$$ is $$P(\operatorname{span}(v_1,v_2)).$$

Two distinct lines in a [[projective plane|Projective subspace]] always intersect in a unique point.